verbose_text: The gammadelta-T cells residing in the lung are potent producers of IL-17 whereas gammadelta-T cells expressing different Vgamma gene segments in the skin, gut, liver, spleen, uterus, and peripheral blood can produce IL-17 or IFN-gamma.
